# Employment by industry by county by SIC|NAICS definition.
There are several employment data source: County Business Patterns(Link:https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/cbp.html), Quarterly Census of Employment and Wages(QCEW)(Link:https://www.bls.gov/cew/), NBER-CES Manufacturing Industry Database(only include manufacturing)(Link:https://www.nber.org/research/data/nber-ces-manufacturing-industry-database).
# Pros and Cons
Pro: covering from 1958-2018
Pro: annual industry-level data
Pro: not only employment, but also output, payroll, input costs, investment, capital stocks, total factor productivity, industry-specific price indexes
Con: not in state/county level
